Milan's is a butter-based cuisine; but olive oil—smoky, lapidary, green, yellow—is honored all over Italy; it is not merely a cooking element but a food in and of itself. Thirteenth-century Florence produced a riddle about the olive (“L'Oliva”):

I am the fair one of the palace field;

I fall to earth, and yet I am not killed;

For that High Lord I go to make a light,

And I am served with love, both day and night.

—translated by Grace Warrack *
